  <div class="container">
    <h2>Everything a chess player needs</h2>
    <p>If you play chess, and love chess, I assume you've tried many things to get better at chess. Tactics trainers, chess lectures, driving hours to private lessons or trying to hack something together online, etc. Well, my friend, look no further, I've got what you need.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="features container">
    <div id="timeline">
      <span id="step-1" class="step">1</span>
      <span id="step-2" class="step">2</span>
      <span id="step-3" class="step">3</span>
    </div>

    <section class="feature">
      <h3>Ability to connect</h3>
      <p>On jackschess.com you can connect with anyone in the world right next to a chessboard. Whether it's your Uncle Charlie or GM Magnus Carlsen, if they accept an invite to your jackschess room, you guys will be connected with a board on the same screen. All in your browser, over the internet.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="feature">
      <h3>The best tools</h3>
      <p>A jackschess room is what every player dreams of. Enjoy Stockfish, which is the best computer in the world giving you analysis when you need it, PGN annotation with notes, PGN uploader, drawing tools, ability to set up and save positions, all in one screen.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="feature">
      <h3>Teachers/learners community</h3>
      <p>The number one best way to learn chess is with others who are better or who want to learn, too. At jackschess we are building a community of teachers looking to help other players, or players looking for instruction from teachers. Contact me if you're looking for a student or a teacher.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="screenshot">
      <img alt="Team-overview" src="/assets/images/marketing/me_and_im.png">
    </div>
  </div>

