    <section>
      <h2>A dream for chess coaches</h2>
      <p>Teaching the game of chess is hard, but it's never the hardest part of being a chess coach, which is super annoying. We've all been there with Skype and ICC/chess.com fighting each other for screen space. Group lessons are a mess. You keep awkwardly looking down to set up puzzles from the book in your lap. The list goes on. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NEN5baraAaQ" target="_blank">Cars are about to start driving themselves</a>; you'd think someone can make something to help chess coaches, right? Yeah, I thought the same too. That's why I built jackschess and designed {{#link-to 'home.signup'}}accounts{{/link-to}} just for coaches. You have your own "chess room" at your own URL with a personalized toolbox of positions, games, puzzles, etc.</p>
    </section>
